<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Beauveria peruviensis" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="peruviensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Beauveria peruviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is practically indistinguishable in morphology to other 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Beauveria" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Beauveria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. The shape and size of the conidia and the colony color of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. peruviensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="peruviensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">B. peruviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among other morphological features have been observed in 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. bassiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="bassiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">B. bassiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. kipukae" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="kipukae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">B. kipukae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. pseudobassiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="pseudobassiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">B. pseudobassiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. varroae" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="varroae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">B. varroae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3852/10-302" author="Rehner, SA" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" pagination="1055 - 1073" refId="B43" refString="Rehner, SA, Minnis, AM, Sung, GH, Luangsa-ard, JJ, Devotto, L, Humber, RA, 2011. Phylogeny and systematics of the anamorphic, entomopathogenic genus Beauveria. Mycologia 103: 1055 - 1073" title="Phylogeny and systematics of the anamorphic, entomopathogenic genus Beauveria." url="https://doi.org/10.3852/10-302" volume="103" year="2011">Rehner et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The lack of diagnostic morphological features to distinguish 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Beauveria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Beauveria peruviensis" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="peruviensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Beauveria peruviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was overcome by delimiting this species with DNA-based methodologies.
</paragraph>
